<answer> \begin{align*}f(x)&=m\tan x\sec x-\tan x +\lambda\tan x\tan 2x -2\cot x\\\\&=m\tan x\sqrt{\tan^2 x +1} -\tan x +\lambda\tan x \tan 2x -2\cot x\\\\&=m\tan x\sqrt{\tan^2 x +1} -\tan x +2\lambda\frac{\tan^2 x-1}{1+\tan^2 x}\tan x- 2\cot x\\\\&=m\tan x\sqrt{\tan^2 x +1} -\tan x +2\lambda\tan x- 2\frac{1}{\tan x}\\\\&=\left(m\sqrt{\tan^2 x +1}-1 +2\lambda\right)\tan x -2\frac{1}{\tan x}\\\text{For }f(x)\text{ to be a linear function we must have}\\\\m&=\pm 1\\\\\lambda&=\frac{1}{2}\\\\\end{align*}
